# Text Elements
Recursive Predictive Parser: 
- maintains the stack implicitly (procedures are called for a non-terminal)
- matching occurs within their corresponding non-terminal procedure
- productions like A->ε is much harder to process. One way is to use it when no other productions can be used. 
This is because we dont know what should be expected beforehand what the next non-ε input looks like if ε is applied.

Non-recursive Predictive Parser (Table driven predictive parser):
- maintains the stack explicitly
- matching occurs in the loop on a condition(when the next item to apply is a terminal)
- nullable productions like A->ε are handled correctly since it can check the table to see if it should be used for a input.


 ^PHn3VB9K

Note: recursive means it uses recursion for applying productions, not that the grammar is recursive.
its more like recursive and iterative ways to build the parser ^ZvrlOW3j

initialisation(configuration):

inputbuffer = inputstr$ ^cUmbipR2

example ^Vqx3p8SS

obsidian://open?vault=Compiler&file=Chapter4%2FPredictive%20Parsing%20Table ^zKxPefWB
